WEBVTT

00:00.758 --> 00:01.737
There are two kinds of folks

00:01.764 --> 00:03.364
who sit around thinking
about how to kill people:

00:03.698 --> 00:05.424
psychopaths
and mystery writers.

00:05.762 --> 00:06.784
I'm the kind that pays better.

00:06.885 --> 00:07.585
Who am I?

00:07.674 --> 00:08.813
I'm Rick Castle.

00:08.814 --> 00:09.214
Castle.

00:09.248 --> 00:09.908
Castle.

00:09.909 --> 00:11.909
I really am ruggedly handsome,
aren't I?

00:12.155 --> 00:14.345
Every writer needs  inspiration.
And I found mine.

00:14.455 --> 00:15.274
Detective Kate Beckett.

00:15.309 --> 00:16.329
- Beckett.
- Beckett.

00:16.364 --> 00:18.270
- Nikki Heat?
- The character he's basing on you.

00:18.316 --> 00:19.802
And thanks to my friendship
with the mayor,

00:19.803 --> 00:20.803
I get to be on her case.

00:20.837 --> 00:22.780
I would be happy
to let you spank me.

00:22.815 --> 00:23.691
And together, we catch killers

00:24.639 --> 00:25.627
We make a pretty
good team, you know?

00:25.728 --> 00:26.728
Like Starsky and Hutch.

00:26.862 --> 00:27.556
Turner and Hooch.

00:27.657 --> 00:29.257
You do remind me
a little of Hooch.

00:29.862 --> 00:30.927
Sophie!

00:30.962 --> 00:32.916
Sophie,
are you in there?

00:32.950 --> 00:35.767
Sophie, the procession starts
in 15 minutes.

00:35.802 --> 00:37.127
If that girl ruins
your wedding--

00:37.128 --> 00:38.828
I'm not worried about
the wedding, mother.

00:39.162 --> 00:40.588
I'm worried about sophie.

00:40.622 --> 00:43.252
If I had as much champagne
as she did last night,

00:43.287 --> 00:45.417
I'd probably be late
for February.

00:45.418 --> 00:46.418
Oh, hey.

00:46.451 --> 00:49.178
Can you open this door for us?
It's an emergency. Please.

00:49.212 --> 00:51.177
Thank you.

00:51.211 --> 00:54.237
♪ ah, it's a crying... ♪

00:54.271 --> 00:56.028
Sophie.

00:56.062 --> 00:57.552
Sophie.

00:57.587 --> 00:59.668
The bed
hasn't been slept in.

00:59.703 --> 01:03.058
♪ it's a crying shame
that the love feels lame ♪

01:03.093 --> 01:04.589
She's not in the bathroom.

01:04.623 --> 01:07.619
Go and see
if her dress is still here.

01:07.654 --> 01:10.317
♪ the love... ♪

01:10.352 --> 01:11.817
Aah!

01:13.981 --> 01:16.146
Make sure it's nice and tight.

01:16.181 --> 01:17.644
Yes, sir.

01:17.679 --> 01:20.110
What on earth
are you two doing?

01:20.145 --> 01:21.042
Research.

01:21.043 --> 01:23.143
Dad has Nikki Heat
duct-taped to a chair

01:23.176 --> 01:24.175
in his next chapter,

01:24.209 --> 01:25.606
and he doesn't know
how to get her out of it.

01:25.641 --> 01:27.140
I thought, what better way
to figure it out

01:27.174 --> 01:28.939
than to get into the mind
of my character.

01:29.040 --> 01:29.840
I don't know.

01:29.874 --> 01:32.505
I suppose you could just use
your imagination.

01:32.706 --> 01:35.006
Well, I want it
to be authentic. Hands.

01:35.007 --> 01:36.007
Mm.

01:36.539 --> 01:38.337
Well, hurry taping up
your father.

01:38.371 --> 01:40.738
We don't want to be late.

01:40.772 --> 01:42.037
Oh, God. I can't believe
I just said that.

01:42.038 --> 01:43.038
Where are you two off to?

01:43.572 --> 01:45.436
Gram's got a dress rehearsal.
I thought I'd go watch.

01:45.437 --> 01:46.137
Watch me

01:46.270 --> 01:48.335
or watch the adorable
delivery boy in the second act?

01:50.370 --> 01:51.536
Too tight?

01:51.937 --> 01:53.137
Perfect.

01:52.970 --> 01:54.536
And you're sure
about your mouth?

01:54.770 --> 01:58.436
Like I said, authentic.

01:59.070 --> 02:00.203
Mm.

02:00.837 --> 02:02.104
Nod if you're okay.

02:02.172 --> 02:05.105
Okay. We're off, and after,
we might go shopping.

02:05.140 --> 02:07.073
So...

02:07.107 --> 02:09.969
You don't mind, right?

02:10.002 --> 02:11.734
Mm.
Oh, come on, dad.

02:11.769 --> 02:13.302
We both know you'd have
no respect for me if I didn't.

02:13.536 --> 02:14.935
Have fun
and good luck.

02:16.670 --> 02:19.635
I don't know where she gets
it from. Honestly, I don't.

02:20.270 --> 02:22.303
Bye.
Adios.

02:23.671 --> 02:26.502
mm.

02:28.000 --> 02:34.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:37.672 --> 02:39.339
mm.

02:39.373 --> 02:41.239
Mm. Oh!

02:43.241 --> 02:44.641
Victim is Sophie Ronson, 35.

02:44.676 --> 02:46.509
She's in from LA
for the wedding.

02:46.510 --> 02:47.510
Was she a guest?

02:47.443 --> 02:48.977
Mnh-mnh. Bridesmaid.

02:51.378 --> 02:52.711
The bride came looking

02:52.746 --> 02:55.179
when Ms. Ronson didn't show up
for her hair and makeup.

02:55.314 --> 02:58.281
Found her
stuffed in that armoire.

02:58.716 --> 02:59.982
What do you see?

02:59.983 --> 03:02.083
Preliminary cause
is asphyxiation.

03:02.117 --> 03:04.051
And from the way
her windpipe is crushed,

03:04.085 --> 03:05.687
I'd say the killer
choked her from behind.

03:06.721 --> 03:08.289
We've got contusions
on her throat,

03:08.323 --> 03:09.924
one of her earrings
is missing.

03:10.558 --> 03:12.759
It looks like it was yanked
from her lobe.

03:12.793 --> 03:15.394
We searched the room.
The earring's not here.

03:15.395 --> 03:17.095
Get CSU
to print out a picture

03:17.129 --> 03:18.429
so that uniforms can start
searching the hotel.

03:18.430 --> 03:19.430
Yeah.

03:20.164 --> 03:21.130
Time of death?

03:21.131 --> 03:23.031
Based on temperature
and lividity,

03:23.165 --> 03:25.330
I'd say between 3:00
and 5:00 am this morning.

03:25.364 --> 03:27.263
- Thank you.
- Hmm.

03:27.297 --> 03:28.830
Let's talk
to hotel security.

03:28.864 --> 03:29.797
I want to see
surveillance tapes

03:29.899 --> 03:31.632
and a list of all
registered hotel guests.

03:31.633 --> 03:33.633
And get records for her
room phone and her cell.

03:33.634 --> 03:34.634
- I'm on it.
- Uh-huh.

03:35.066 --> 03:37.267
Hotel says only one key card
was issued to the victim.

03:37.301 --> 03:39.602
It was last used to enter
the victim's room at 3:18 am.

03:39.603 --> 03:41.403
Okay, well, that coincides
with time of death.

03:41.636 --> 03:42.937
Where are the bride and groom?

03:42.938 --> 03:44.138
Bridal suite
at the end of the hall.

03:44.171 --> 03:46.138
Uh, Greg Andyra.

03:46.139 --> 03:48.139
Okay, have uniforms assemble
the wedding guests

03:48.173 --> 03:49.141
in the bar to be interviewed.

03:49.142 --> 03:50.142
Where's Castle?

03:50.143 --> 03:52.043
I don't know. Figured
the death of a bridesmaid

03:52.076 --> 03:53.143
would be right up his alley.

03:53.144 --> 03:55.244
He heard "wedding"
and probably got cold feet?

03:56.745 --> 03:57.845
Hmm.

04:05.751 --> 04:07.117
Huh.

04:09.486 --> 04:11.488
Attaboy, Rick.

04:11.522 --> 04:13.688
Huh.

04:16.524 --> 04:18.957
When was the last time
that you saw Sophie?

04:18.992 --> 04:20.958
At the rehearsal dinner
last night.

04:21.791 --> 04:23.092
I don't even think
I talked to her.

04:24.127 --> 04:25.326
She came all this way
for us,

04:25.361 --> 04:27.195
and I don't think
I even said hello.

04:27.229 --> 04:30.530
It's not your fault, Kyra.
It was a crazy day.

04:30.565 --> 04:33.099
Did you talk to her
after I went up to bed?

04:33.134 --> 04:35.468
No. You know
how uncle Teddy is.

04:35.503 --> 04:37.503
He wouldn't let me leave
without doing tequila shots.

04:38.238 --> 04:40.038
I escaped up to my room
around 1:00.

04:40.573 --> 04:42.373
I'm not sure if Sophie
was still at the bar.

04:42.808 --> 04:44.142
The two of you weren't
in the same room last night?

04:44.443 --> 04:45.443
No.

04:45.676 --> 04:47.943
It's bad luck to see the bride
before the wedding.

04:49.944 --> 04:51.844
Is there anything else
you can tell me about Sophie?

04:52.347 --> 04:54.850
Was she in a relationship?
Did she have any enemies?

04:54.884 --> 04:56.319
I don't know.

04:56.353 --> 05:00.292
She lived in LA, and we--
we were never super close.

05:00.326 --> 05:01.630
Sophie introduced us.

05:02.031 --> 05:03.431
She's the reason we're together.

05:03.432 --> 05:05.332
So when we were planning
the wedding,

05:05.364 --> 05:06.898
we thought
she should be there.

05:06.933 --> 05:09.200
But the engagement party was
the first time we'd seen her

05:09.235 --> 05:12.437
in a couple of years,
and now she's dead.

05:12.472 --> 05:14.940
Who would do
something like this?

05:14.974 --> 05:17.309
That's what we're here
to find out.

05:17.343 --> 05:18.777
Here you go.

05:18.811 --> 05:20.379
Thanks, Joe. That's great.

05:20.413 --> 05:21.747
Hotel security?

05:21.781 --> 05:23.782
Yeah. They do background checks
on all their employees.

05:23.817 --> 05:26.185
seemed pretty sure there wasn't
a killer among them,

05:26.219 --> 05:28.253
but he gave me the list.

05:28.288 --> 05:29.688
He's also pulling
the surveillance tapes.

05:29.722 --> 05:32.291
Good news is, the elevators are
all wired. Bad news is,

05:32.325 --> 05:33.860
the stairwells
and hallways aren't.

05:35.495 --> 05:36.764
Oh, look who it is.

05:36.765 --> 05:38.665
We were about to send out
a search party. Where you been?

05:38.698 --> 05:40.966
Uh, I got a little tied up with work.
Hmm.

05:41.000 --> 05:43.335
-Which way to the crime scene?
- Sixth floor.

05:43.369 --> 05:44.970
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm. Hey.

05:45.004 --> 05:47.940
Bro... is that duct tape
on your pants?

05:47.974 --> 05:50.276
Hmm.

05:50.310 --> 05:53.612
Yes. Yes, it is.

05:54.981 --> 05:56.948
So a bridesmaid, huh?

05:56.983 --> 05:58.483
What happened?

05:58.517 --> 06:00.385
Wouldn't get caught
dead in that dress?

06:00.419 --> 06:02.354
they're actually
not that bad.

06:02.388 --> 06:05.556
A subtle mauve chiffon.
Dude, really? Mauve?

06:05.590 --> 06:06.991
What? I have sisters.

06:07.025 --> 06:08.928
You should've seen
their dresses--hideous.

06:08.962 --> 06:10.963
Ah, bridesmaid dresses
are supposed to be hideous.

06:10.964 --> 06:11.964
Really, why?

06:11.998 --> 06:13.931
So that the bride looks
more beautiful in comparison.

06:13.932 --> 06:14.932
Ah, see?

06:14.966 --> 06:17.699
Not a woman alive who doesn't
think about her wedding day,

06:17.733 --> 06:18.901
not even Kate Beckett.

06:18.935 --> 06:20.869
Tell me you never tore
a picture of a wedding gown

06:20.904 --> 06:22.072
out of a magazine.

06:22.373 --> 06:23.773
I've never torn a picture
of a wedding gown

06:23.806 --> 06:24.941
out of a magazine.

06:26.942 --> 06:28.142
You're lying.

06:28.476 --> 06:29.276
- She's lying.
- Mm-hmm.

06:29.310 --> 06:30.977
Mm-hmm.

06:38.152 --> 06:39.586
So who's the unlucky bride?

06:39.620 --> 06:42.455
Uh, her name is...

06:42.490 --> 06:44.591
Kyra?

06:47.928 --> 06:49.529
Rick?

06:52.531 --> 06:54.033
Rick Castle.

06:54.067 --> 06:55.968
You two know each other?

06:56.003 --> 06:58.604
That would be
an understatement.

